We can solve for $m$ by isolating it. Since the two rate expressions are equivalent, their reciprocals are also equivalent.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{m \text{ minutes}}{52 \text{ km}}&=\dfrac{85 \text{ minutes}}{20 \text{ km}} \\\\
m \text{ minutes}&=\dfrac{85 \text{ minutes}}{20 \cancel{\text{ km}}}\cdot{52 \cancel{\text{ km}}}
\end{align}$
